headline: Big Oil Isn’t Budging on Output as OPEC+ Supply Hike Looms
summary: (Bloomberg) -- The largest western oil producers are mostly sticking with their growth plans for now, despite a 16% decline in crude prices during April and a decision by OPEC+ to crank up output in June.Most Read from BloombergThe Battle Over the Fate of Detroit’s Renaissance CenterNYC Lost $9 Billion of Income to Miami, Palm Beach in Five YearsNYC Real Estate Industry Asks Judge to Block New Broker Fee LawNJ Transit Strike Would Be ‘Disaster’ for Region, Sherrill SaysNJ Transit Urges Commuters
